{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:25:55.100850+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The README already contains the complete table of implemented CIFAR-10 models with their reported accuracy. Here it is:\n\n| Model | Accuracy |\n| --- | --- |\n| [VGG16](https://arxiv.org/abs/1409.1556) | 92.64% |\n| [ResNet18](https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385) | 93.02% |\n| [ResNet50](https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385) | 93.62% |\n| [ResNet101](https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385) | 93.75% |\n| [RegNetX_200MF](https://arxiv.org/abs/2003.13678) | 94.24% |\n| [RegNetY_400MF](https://arxiv.org/abs/2003.13678) | 94.29% |\n| [MobileNetV2](https://arxiv.org/abs/1801.04381) | 94.43% |\n| [ResNeXt29(32x4d)](https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.05431) | 94.73% |\n| [ResNeXt29(2x64d)](https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.05431) | 94.82% |\n| [SimpleDLA](https://arxiv.org/abs/1707.064) | 94.89% |\n| [DenseNet121](https://arxiv.org/abs/1608.06993) | 95.04% |\n| [PreActResNet18](https://arxiv.org/abs/1603.05027) | 95.11% |\n| [DPN92](https://arxiv.org/abs/1707.01629) | 95.16% |\n| [DLA](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1707.06484.pdf) | 95.47% |\n\n**Note:** The `models/` directory also contains implementations for LeNet, SENet, PNASNet, GoogleNet, ShuffleNet, ShuffleNetV2, MobileNet, and EfficientNet, but no accuracy results are reported for these in the README. The 14 models listed above are the ones with documented CIFAR-10 accuracy.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 947, "prompt_tokens": 12538, "total_tokens": 13485, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 323, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 12032}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "d98cbede9c3048939aa1015739f7de91", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": nul